cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with a computer vision task of human parsing, which involves segmenting a human image into semantic regions. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a new model that combines parametric and non-parametric approaches, which involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) and K Nearest Neighbor (KNN) algorithms. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves image retrieval and matching, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
